long_desc.thetext:
Same for e4's @Inject and javax.inject.Inject
@Inject(option=true) indicates that the injector does not necessarily change the field value. Such an annotation should be ignored. Fields that are explicitly annotated with @Nullable and @Inject may be injected with a null value. Otherwise the value should be treated as definitely non null. I think an @NonNullByDefault(false) should not be applied to @Inject fields, that are not annotated explicitly as Nullable.
see also http://code.google.com/p/google-guice/wiki/UseNullable
